The evidence with the title 'I was right: under Obama, spending has been flat - MarketWatch ' says Nov 6, 2013  ... Last week , the Treasury Department announced that federal spending fell 2.3% to $ 3.45 trillion in fiscal 2013 after dropping 1.8% in 2012. It was the largest annual decline in federal spending since 1955 , and the first time spending had fallen two years in a row since 1954 - 55 , at the end of the KoreanWar.
